OL,3,CStudents training to teach 'priority'
OL,4,Csubjects to receive an extra #5,000
OL,6,FEnglish, which is a core subject for
OL,7,Fnon-Welsh Secondary Schools in Wales,
OL,8,Fis not on the list of eligible key
OL,9,Fsubjects.
OL,11,FThe current ITE incentive scheme
OL,12,Foffers a grant of up to #15,000 for
OL,13,Fpriority subjects and this is now set
OL,14,Fto increase by #5,000.
OL,16,FBut a teaching union has dubbed the
OL,17,Fmove a "sticking plaster" that risks
OL,18,Fcreating a two-tier workforce.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G2/5
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,437,430,260,120,000,100
PN,43603
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F436A1781453487
OL,3,CStudents training to teach 'priority'
OL,4,Csubjects to receive an extra #5,000
OL,6,FThe National Association of
OL,7,FHeadteachers (NAHT) said it agrees a
OL,8,Fdetailed plan is needed to help
OL,9,Fschools, but focusing on subject-
OL,10,Fspecific is not the way to go.
OL,12,FLaura Doel, national secretary of
OL,13,Fschool leaders' union, said: "This
OL,14,Frisks creating a two-tier workforce
OL,15,Fand appears to be a short-term
OL,16,Fsticking plaster solution for a
OL,17,Fsystemic problem.
OL,26,@uD@^OU
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G3/5
